@flexiarg futon-theory/futonic-logic
@title Futonic Logic: Vocabulary, Composition, and the Recognition Loop
@sigils [🧂/鹽]
@keywords futonic, logic, composition, articulation, salience, evaluation, regulator, individuation, s-expression
@audience futon developers, pattern theorists, war room
@tone analytic-foundational
@factor Keen investigation (dhammavicaya)
@style specification
@references [futon-theory/symbolic-individuation futon-theory/four-types futon-theory/theory-as-exotype futon-theory/structural-tension-as-observation futon-theory/retroactive-canonicalization futon-theory/baldwin-cycle futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/agent-contract]

! conclusion: 
  Futonic logic specifies the vocabulary, composition rules, and recognition
  loop that futon-theory patterns presuppose. It does not replace the patterns;
  it makes explicit the symbolic operations they perform implicitly. The
  central insight: composition (鹽) is not concatenation but the recognition
  that latent potential (鹵) and stabilizing interface (皿) are available
  under the same decomposition regime (部). The futonic loop — input, decompose,
  articulate, compose, sense, regulate, act, evaluate — is the abstract form
  of the PSR→PUR cycle and the derivation xenotype alike.

  == 0. META-SYNTAX ==

  ⿱ denotes top-bottom composition in glyph space. Futonically, it
  corresponds to a binary articulation whose abstract form is (CAR . CDR):

  (meta-syntax
    (⿱
      (role layout-operator)
      (maps-to cons)
      (explanation
        "⿱ denotes top-bottom composition in glyph space;
         futonically, it corresponds to a binary articulation
         whose abstract form is (CAR . CDR).")))

  This does NOT assert that all composition is binary. It asserts only: when
  ⿱ appears, interpret it as a historically successful binary articulation,
  abstractable as a cons pair. Triads, polycentric forms, and n-ary
  decompositions operate under other 部.

  == 1. VOCABULARY ==

  Core symbols declared as roles, not definitions. Premature semantic collapse
  is the vocabulary equivalent of forward-declaration debt (social/verify-
  before-compose): fixing meaning before structure is verified produces
  symbols that cannot compose.

  (vocabulary
    (象  (role configuration)
         (note "A structured whole that can be referenced without full
                expansion. First-class, carryable, transformable."))
    (部  (role decomposition-regime)
         (note "A chosen regime of articulation, not an ontological given.
                Arity-variable: binary, triadic, polycentric."))
    (咅  (role articulation)
         (note "The act of making a decomposition explicit. Not analysis
                (which presumes correctness) but perception of structure
                already present."))
    (香  (role embodied-salience)
         (note "Cross-layer perception that signals without full
                formalization. Agent-relative. Defeasible."))
    (味  (role embodied-evaluation)
         (note "Selection by felt difference rather than proof. The
                evaluative counterpart of 香."))
    (鹽  (role generative-composition)
         (note "Composition that generates: not mere juxtaposition but
                the recognition that potential and container are available
                under the same 部."))
    (鹵  (role latent-substrate)
         (note "Manipulable potential. What can be transformed if a 皿
                is available to receive the result."))
    (皿  (role stabilizing-container)
         (note "Interface, vessel, boundary. What receives and stabilizes
                the product of transformation."))
    (間  (role honest-interval)
         (note "The structured space between components, perceived
                without premature filling. 間 is not emptiness —
                it is the topological fact that an interval exists
                and has properties that must be read, not generated.
                Hallucinating content into 間 produces false salience
                and brittle composition."))
    (関  (role gate-relation)
         (note "Barrier, gate, typed connection. 関 is the structural
                fact that components are related through constraints,
                not mere adjacency. A gate pipeline is a chain of 関;
                a core.logic relation is 関 made evaluable; a typed
                port (mission-interface-signature) is 関 at a boundary.
                関 formalizes what 間 perceives: the interval has
                structure, and that structure can be traversed or
                blocked. 間 reads the gap; 関 names the gate.
                Together (無門関): the gate that dissolves when
                honestly perceived — tension discovery as navigation."))
    (既  (role earned-past)
         (note "Urðr: that-which-has-come-to-pass. Not mere temporal
                before, but the load-bearing past — closure-evidence,
                HEAD-as-escrow, the proof-path's earned record.
                Citeable, structurally available to the present, and
                rewritable only with traces. (See futon-theory/wyrd.)"))
    (化  (role becoming-event)
         (note "Verðandi: in-process-of-happening, the present
                participle of weorþan ('to come to pass'). The live
                writer-action, the consent gate firing, the loop
                presently composing. Distinct from 未知: 未知 is the
                epistemic three-valuedness of in-flight state, while
                化 is the temporal becoming itself. Every 化 emits
                (應 . 債)."))
    (應  (role modal-obligation)
         (note "Skuld (modal face): the 'ought / shall / should'
                voice. Cognate with English shall/should via Germanic
                *skul-. 應 is what the present says about what the
                future must do; not yet a debt-record but a modal
                claim. Sorries are stated in the voice of 應."))
    (債  (role substantive-debt)
         (note "Skuld (substantive face): debt incurred. Every act
                of 鹽 (composition) emits 債 alongside salt-pay
                (worth, from salarium). sorrys.edn is the registry
                of 債 at proof-path granularity; mission scope-remaining
                tracks 債 at mission granularity. 債 outstanding in
                regime A may be 鹽 generative in regime B — this
                trans-regime survival is wyrd-salience
                (futon-theory/wyrd)."))
    (未知 (role non-equilibrium-interval)
         (note "Actionable but not predictable. Three-valued logic:
                the system is neither in its prior state nor in its
                successor state."))
    (非死非活 (role non-terminal-state)
         (note "System is responsive but not self-sustaining. Equivalent
                to 未知 at the lifecycle level."))
    (🔮  (role regulator)
         (note "Capacity to act within 未知 while modulating action
                amplitude. Components: 能 (capacity) + 捨 (setting-down).")))

  == 2. COMPOSITIONAL STRUCTURE ==

  2.1 象 and 部:

  (象
    (status first-class)
    (properties (carryable transformable))
    (note "A structured whole that can be referenced without full expansion."))

  (部
    (function bounded-decomposition)
    (arity-variable true)
    (examples (binary triadic polycentric))
    (note "A chosen regime of articulation, not an ontological given."))

  2.2 鹽 as composition:

  (鹽
    (structure (⿱ 鹵 皿))
    (abstract-form (cons 鹵 皿))
    (interpretation
      (鹵 (latent manipulable potential))
      (皿 (interface container stabilizer)))
    (constraint
      "Generativity requires both terms to be available under the same 部."))

  2.3 Salience as the appearance of 鹽:

  (compositional-salience
    (depends-on 鹽)
    (definition
      "Agent-relative perception that a (鹵 . 皿) decomposition
       is presently actionable."))

  (A7-precondition
    (if (perceives-間 agent interval))
    (then (A7 may proceed: test for 鹵 and 皿))
    (else (composition is premature: the interval has not
           been honestly observed)))

  (A7
    (precondition A7-precondition)
    (if (exists (鹽 (⿱ 鹵 皿))))
    (and (perceivable 鹵) (perceivable 皿))
    (then (salience emerges))
    (else (generativity remains inert)))

  2.4 香 and 味:

  (香
    (role cross-layer-perception)
    (function "Signals salience without full formalization."))

  (味
    (role embodied-selection)
    (function "Evaluates articulations by felt difference rather than proof."))

  2.5 🔮 and 捨:

  (🔮
    (components (能 捨))
    (function regulator)
    (definition
      "Capacity to act within 未知 while modulating action amplitude."))

  (捨
    (operation set-down)
    (precondition (has 🔮))
    (effect
      "Reduce deployed capacity to limit harm while preserving
       reversibility."))

  2.6 未知 and 非死非活:

  (未知
    (state non-equilibrium)
    (logic three-valued)
    (properties (actionable not-predictable)))

  (非死非活
    (equivalence 未知)
    (note "System is responsive but not self-sustaining."))

  2.7 既 / 化 / 應 / 債 — The Three-Time Decomposition:

  The three Norns (Urðr, Verðandi, Skuld) constitute a three-time
  projection of every present moment. See futon-theory/wyrd for
  the etymological grounding (wyrd ← weorþan ← PIE *wert-) and
  the Skuld≈SORRY identification.

  (three-time-decomposition
    (frame (Norns Urðr Verðandi Skuld))
    (glyphs (既 化 (應 . 債)))
    (note "Decomposes the present moment into already-completed,
           presently-becoming, and owed-to-the-future aspects.
           Not a temporal sequence but a simultaneous three-face
           projection of every loop turn. The Buddhist 三時
           (過去/現在/未來) is too neutral here; it loses Skuld's
           owed character, collapsing future-as-debt into
           future-as-next."))

  (Skuld-pair
    (structure (⿱ 應 債))
    (interpretation
      (應 (modal voice of obligation: ought, shall))
      (債 (substantive record of debt incurred)))
    (constraint "Premature collapse to 應 alone is anxiety
                 (debt voiced but unrecorded); to 債 alone is
                 bookkeeping (debt without standing modal force).
                 Both faces are required."))

  (three-time-rule
    (each (loop-turn t))
    (projects-onto
      (既 (closure-evidence-available-at t))
      (化 (composition-presently-firing-at t))
      ((應 . 債) (obligations-emitted-by-firing)))
    (note "No turn is wholly any one face. Collapse to 既 alone
           is nostalgia (citing past with no present act); to 化
           alone is amnesia (acting without grounding); to (應 . 債)
           alone is anxiety/accounting without grounding or act."))

  2.8 鹽 / 債 — The Composition-Debt Ledger:

  Composition has two sides: what it pays (salt, salarium, worth)
  and what it owes (Skuld, 債, shall). 鹽 (existing §2.2) is the
  generative side. 債 is the dual obligation side. The pair forms
  the ledger every loop turn must keep.

  (compositional-ledger
    (form (⿱ 鹽 債))
    (credit-side
      (worth "salt-money: the salt-pay")
      (provenance "Roman salarium → English salary → 'worth one's salt'"))
    (debit-side
      (debt 債)
      (provenance "Germanic *skul- → Old Norse Skuld → English shall/should"))
    (rule
      (every-鹽 emits (worth . 債))
      (note "No composition completes its bookkeeping in a single
             部 — the 債 outstanding in regime A may be the 鹽
             generative in regime B. This trans-regime survival
             IS wyrd-salience (futon-theory/wyrd)."))
    (cross-linguistic-triangulation
      (Latin salarium)
      (Chinese (鹽 債))
      (Old-English (wyrd weorþan Skuld-via-Norse))
      (note "Three independent linguistic registers triangulate
             the same ledger structure. The triangulation is itself
             a wyrd-survival test passing: when the same structure
             is recovered from three unrelated source languages,
             it is not an artifact of any one language's idioms.")))

  (ledger-anti-collapse
    (anti-pattern "Collapse the ledger to net.")
    (reason "Net hides structure: 鹽 in regime A and 債 in regime
             B do not sum to zero — they are the wyrd-salient
             configuration that the present must continue to turn
             (vertere) between regimes to keep legible. Net-bookkeeping
             is the 'mere X' move applied to the ledger itself."))

  == 3. THE FUTONIC LOOP ==

  (futonic-loop
    (input 象)
    (choose 部)
    (articulate 咅)
    (if (forms (鹽 (⿱ 鹵 皿))))
    (and (sense 香) (regulate 🔮))
    (then
      (act-within 未知)
      (evaluate 味))
    (else
      (apply 捨)))

  3.1 Three-Time Projection of the Loop:

  Each loop turn projects onto all three Nornic faces simultaneously.
  The loop above describes the becoming-firing (化); the three-time
  projection makes explicit what authorises it (既) and what it
  emits (應 . 債).

  (loop-three-time-projection
    (at-every-turn t
      (既-at-t
        (proof-path-history-before-t)
        (earned-evidence-citeable-at-t)
        (HEAD-as-escrow-at-t))
      (化-at-t
        (the-rule-itself §3-futonic-loop)
        (presently-firing 咅)
        (presently-composing 鹽))
      ((應 . 債)-at-t
        (sorries-registered-during-t)
        (follow-on-modal-commitments)
        (discharge-due-by τ))))

  (loop-and-ledger
    (every-step (or 鹽 捨))
    (emits ledger-entry
           (credit (or 香 味-confirms))
           (debit (應 . 債)))
    (note "The futonic loop is a Nornic engine: it inherits 既 as
           authorisation, composes in 化, emits (應 . 債) as
           consequence. The else-branch (捨) is explicit handling
           of obligation without further commitment — the modal
           應 'we ought not act' applied to limit 債 accumulation."))

  == 4. GROUNDING IN ACTUAL USAGE ==

  Every symbol in the vocabulary has been used (implicitly or explicitly)
  across futon missions. This section makes those uses explicit. The logic
  is practical because we have been practising it.

  4.1 象 — Configuration

  | Context | 象 instance | Evidence |
  | Wiring diagram | coordination-exotype.edn | A structured whole: 6 inputs, 6 outputs, 10 components, 30 edges. Referenceable as ":coordination-exotype" without expansion. |
  | Flexiarg pattern | mandatory-psr.flexiarg | A structured whole: conclusion, context, IF/HOWEVER/THEN/BECAUSE. Carryable by pattern-id. |
  | Proof path | gate pipeline output | A structured whole: linked PSR→PUR→PAR chain. Transformable (L1 scans it for tensions). |
  | Session | Claude Code session | A structured whole: context, tools, history. Compresses (compaction) but remains referenceable. |

  4.2 部 — Decomposition Regime

  | Context | 部 instance | Evidence |
  | Three-futon split | timescale decomposition | 部 = timescale boundaries (social/task/glacial). Not chosen but perceived (symbolic-individuation). |
  | Gate pipeline | six-gate decomposition | 部 = the six gates G5→G0. Binary at each gate (pass/reject), hexadic in composition. |
  | Derivation xenotype | six-step decomposition | 部 = IDENTIFY→MAP→DERIVE→ARGUE→VERIFY→INSTANTIATE. Sequential, not arbitrary. |
  | Baldwin cycle | triadic decomposition | 部 = NAMING→SELECTION→CANALIZATION. Three phases, not two or four. |

  4.3 咅 — Articulation

  | Context | 咅 instance | Evidence |
  | PSR | pattern selection | The agent makes a decomposition explicit: "I will use this pattern for this task." |
  | ARGUMENT.flexiarg | claim composition | Each S/R/T/C section articulates: makes a claim's structure visible. |
  | Mission scoping | scope in/out | The mission author articulates: what's inside, what's outside. |
  | Git commit | change articulation | The commit message articulates: what changed and why. |

  4.4 鹽 — Generative Composition (鹵 + 皿)

  | Context | 鹵 (potential) | 皿 (container) | 鹽 (composition) |
  | Gate pipeline | Pattern library (potential approaches) | Gate shapes (Malli schemas) | Validated proof-path (generative: produces evidence) |
  | L1 canonicalizer | Observed tensions (potential patterns) | Library format (flexiarg structure) | New pattern in library (generative: constrains future work) |
  | Social exotype | Agency/realtime patterns (potential requirements) | Wiring diagram format (edn structure) | Validated social-exotype.edn (generative: enables implementation) |
  | Session | Prior knowledge + context | PSR/PUR protocol (recording structure) | Auditable session (generative: feeds glacial loop) |

  4.5 香 — Embodied Salience

  | Context | 香 instance | Evidence |
  | Pattern search | futon3a notions/compass | Signals "this pattern might apply" without proving it. ANN + GloVe similarity, not logical implication. |
  | Hotword matching | patterns-index.tsv hotwords | "deliver" fires on "delivery-receipt" — salience signal, not identification. |
  | Tension scanning | L1-observe structural-irritation | "This gap-PSR has appeared 3 times" — cross-layer perception that something recurs, without naming what. |
  | Git archaeology | commit pattern recognition | "These 5 commits all fix forward-declarations" — perceiving a pattern before it has a name. |

  4.6 味 — Embodied Evaluation

  | Context | 味 instance | Evidence |
  | PUR | pattern use record | Evaluates by outcome (prediction-error), not by proof. "Did using this pattern help?" is 味, not formal verification. |
  | Mana bins | sospeso confidence bins | p ∈ {0.3, 0.6, 0.8, 0.95} — discrete bins to "reduce self-deception." Evaluation by felt confidence, not computed probability. |
  | ct/mission.clj | 8/8 checks pass | Evaluation by structural test, not semantic proof. The diagram is well-formed; whether it's the right diagram is 味. |
  | Code review | Codex review comments | "This could be more defensive" — evaluative judgement, not provable claim. |

  4.7 🔮 — Regulator (能 + 捨)

  | Context | 能 (capacity) | 捨 (setting-down) | 🔮 (regulation) |
  | Sospeso protocol | Confidence p · C spent on action | (1-p) · C donated to pool + blast radius note | Proceed at lower confidence with bounded harm |
  | Gate rejection | Pipeline can process the request | Gate rejects with typed error + gate attribution | Fail fast, preserve reversibility |
  | Mission parking | Team could continue the subsystem | :active → :blocked with recorded blocker | Explicit exit over silent abandonment |
  | Context compaction | LLM has N tokens of context | Older context compressed to summary | Continue operating with reduced but sufficient state |

  4.8 未知 / 非死非活

  | Context | Instance | Evidence |
  | Abandoned missions | Forum: 8 commits, no exit, no :blocked | Neither done (:done) nor explicitly blocked (:blocked). Responsive to git log but not self-sustaining. |
  | Sospeso interval | Between action and verification | The action has been taken (at p < 0.95) but outcome is not yet verified. System is in 未知. |
  | futon3c pre-implementation | ARGUMENT written, exotype validated, no code | The social loop is specified but not instantiated. Non-equilibrium: the argument creates obligations the code hasn't satisfied. |
  | Context boundary | Between session compaction and new turn | The LLM has lost detailed context but retains summary. Actionable but not fully predictable. |

  4.9 間 — Honest Interval

  | Context | 間 instance | Evidence |
  | Tension discovery | gap between devmap component and mission inventory | Tension browser reads 間: "peripheral-gauntlet/C-arena has no mission." The gap is structural, not empty — it has a devmap, a gate position, dependencies. Reading it honestly (not filling it) produces the correct next action. |
  | futon1→futon1a porting | gap between declared invariants and implementations | "entity-lifecycle and referential-integrity were not ported." 間 perceived too late: the gap was filled with the assumption "it was ported" — false salience from hallucinated content. |
  | A7-precondition | interval between 鹵 (potential) and 皿 (container) | Before composing, perceive whether the interval actually exists. A pattern library and a recording protocol may be adjacent without composing — 間 is the honest observation that composition hasn't happened yet. |
  | Code→docs hypergraph | gap between computed links and persisted links | futon4's finder strategies compute links in Emacs hash tables. 間 is the honest observation that the links are not persisted — the gap between working model and durable fact. |

  4.10 関 — Gate / Relation

  | Context | 関 instance | Evidence |
  | Peripheral gauntlet | G0→G7 gate pipeline | Each gate is a 関: a typed barrier with acceptance criteria. C-arena (Gate 0) must pass before C-umwelt (Gate 1) can begin. The chain of 関 IS the peripheral gauntlet. |
  | core.logic relations | `coverso`, `componento`, `invarianto` | Each pldb/db-rel is a 関: a typed connection between facts. `(coverso mid comp-id)` IS the gate between "component exists" and "component is addressed." |
  | mission-interface-signature | typed input/output ports | Every port is a 関 at a boundary: what the system exposes, typed, constrained. A box with no typed ports cannot participate in composition — missing 関. |
  | Hyperedge endpoints | `devmap:X`, `component:X/Y`, `mission:Z` | Each endpoint is a 関 connecting the hyperedge to the entities it relates. Queryable: "find all 関 that touch component C-arena." |
  | Tension→path trace | claim → mission → evidence → var → source | The full path is a chain of 関: each step is a typed gate. When all gates pass (can be traversed), the claim is grounded. When a gate blocks, that's a tension. |

  4.11 間 + 関 → 無門関 (The Gateless Gate)

  Tension discovery is 間 + 関 composed: read the gap honestly (間), then
  traverse the gate structure (関) to find what the gap implies. The "gateless
  gate" is not the absence of gates — it is the perception that the gate
  dissolves when the interval is honestly read. The tension "C-arena has no
  mission" IS the gate: traversing it (proposing the mission, tracing the
  path) is how it opens. The barrier and the path are the same structure
  seen from different sides of 間.

  In operational terms: `query-uncovered-components` (core.logic) reads 間
  relationally; `trace-tension-path` (futon3c) traverses the chain of 関
  from tension to source. The composition of these two operations IS the
  self-representing stack's discovery loop — and it should be invocable
  on demand, not performed ad hoc.

  4.12 既 — Earned Past (Urðr)

  | Context | 既 instance | Evidence |
  | Proof path | committed PSR→PUR→PAR chain | The chain is 既: citeable as authority, extensible by future loops, rewritable only with explicit trace |
  | HEAD-as-escrow | git HEAD as held-truth | HEAD is 既 in the most literal sense: what has come to pass, held as the present's grounding |
  | Closure evidence | mission-close artifact | Closure freezes a 化 into citeable 既; the closure record is the artifact through which future loops cite the closed mission |
  | Library canonicalization | promoted flexiarg | Promotion turns a candidate-pattern into 既: subsequent loops cite it as ground rather than candidate |
  | Frozen tape (piano roll) | append-only PSR/PUR/PAR log | The roll IS the Urðr-surface: what cannot be un-done, only added to |

  4.13 化 — Becoming Event (Verðandi)

  | Context | 化 instance | Evidence |
  | Live writer-action | VSATARCS-writer presently firing | The act of composition is 化: not yet 既, not yet emitting 債, but in the act |
  | Consent gate firing | gate evaluating an action class | The firing moment IS 化: not the gate's config (genotype) nor its outcome (phenotype), but the becoming-event |
  | PSR being authored | agent presently choosing a pattern | The choosing is 化; the recorded choice is 既; the verification obligation is (應 . 債) |
  | Loop turn | one execution of the futonic loop | Each turn IS 化 for the duration of its firing; afterward it has become 既 |
  | M-live-geometric-stack | the live geometric surface | The Verðandi-surface of the futon stack: live (T, ∇, Δ, drift) |

  4.14 應 / 債 — Owed Obligation (Skuld)

  | Context | 應 instance | 債 instance | Evidence |
  | sorrys.edn | "we should X" voice in entry text | typed debt record with :kind | 應 is the modal voice; 債 is the structural debt the registry tracks |
  | Mission scoping | "this mission shall deliver Y" | uncompleted scoped commitments | 應 in scope language; 債 in scope-remaining accounting |
  | Pattern next-steps | next[…] entries | unfulfilled pattern-promises | Modal commitments (應) become structural debts (債) if not discharged |
  | Wiring obligations | invariant statement | broken invariant under load | 應 declares what should hold; 債 is what actually breaks |
  | sorrys.edn :kind | :prototyping-forward vs :technical-debt | distinct debt-classes | 債 typed by :kind; collapse to one class hides regime distinctions |

  == 5. THE FUTONIC LOOP IN PRACTICE ==

  The abstract loop (§3) maps onto three concrete cycles:

  5.1 PSR→PUR cycle (per-task):

  (futonic-loop
    (input   象  := task request entering the gate pipeline)
    (choose  部  := select decomposition: which gate, which timescale)
    (articulate 咅 := write PSR: choose a pattern, commit to an approach)
    (if (forms 鹽) := pattern (鹵) + evidence shape (皿) compose)
    (and (sense 香) := during execution, perceive whether it's working)
    (and (regulate 🔮) := stay within budget, reject if budget exceeded)
    (then
      (act-within 未知 := execute under uncertainty)
      (evaluate 味 := write PUR: evaluate outcome by felt difference))
    (else
      (apply 捨 := reject at gate, park mission, write PAR)))

  5.2 Derivation xenotype (per-mission):

  (futonic-loop
    (input   象  := domain to be derived: "social coordination")
    (choose  部  := IDENTIFY the decomposition regime: git archaeology,
                    pattern audit, devmap review)
    (articulate 咅 := MAP + DERIVE: articulate patterns and requirements
                    from the evidence)
    (if (forms 鹽) := ARGUE: requirements (鹵) + argument structure (皿)
                    compose into a valid case)
    (and (sense 香) := during argument construction, perceive convergences)
    (and (regulate 🔮) := VERIFY: check invariants, validate diagrams)
    (then
      (act-within 未知 := INSTANTIATE: build the code)
      (evaluate 味 := tests pass, 8/8 checks, round-trip proof))
    (else
      (apply 捨 := park mission, record blocker, explicit exit)))

  5.3 Glacial loop (per-library-evolution):

  (futonic-loop
    (input   象  := accumulated proof paths from many tasks)
    (choose  部  := L1-observe: which tension criterion to scan?
                    structural-irritation / pre-symbolic-pressure /
                    trans-situational-reappearance)
    (articulate 咅 := name the tension: a recurring pattern emerges)
    (if (forms 鹽) := tension observation (鹵) + flexiarg format (皿)
                    compose into a candidate pattern)
    (and (sense 香) := does this tension appear across contexts?)
    (and (regulate 🔮) := does it meet the canonicalization threshold?
                    frequency >= 3, contexts >= 2)
    (then
      (act-within 未知 := write new flexiarg to library)
      (evaluate 味 := subsequent G3 accepts the new pattern))
    (else
      (apply 捨 := tension does not meet threshold, record but do not
                    canonicalize)))

